1[章/しょう]チュートリアル[試合/しあい] [雷/らい][門/もん][中/ちゅう]
Description 1 of the Nagumo Hara Soccer Club.
Description 2 of the Nagumo Hara Soccer Club.
A rising team formed recently, they used smart tactics to\nbreak into Football Frontier and topple prestigious teams.
Their smart training sharpens every player's tactical vision,\nearning them the nickname "Perfect Football Northbright."
A top academic rival to <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>,\nthey surged forward once a skilled coordinator joined their ranks.
They risk using Keshin despite the toll it takes,\nmaking their tactic rare and tough for others to counter.
Led by a prodigy dubbed "Alice in Footballand,"\nthey dominate with flawless teamwork and perfect tactics.
A girls' school in Kumamoto with perfect teamwork.\nNobody knows who leads, sparking rumors of a secret "Queen Bee."
Two Fukuoka schools merged into this team. Lots of tough-looking kids,\nbut it's just an act to push back against forced evictions.
A gang of rough kids from <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> formed this team. When\ntheir old manager died, he bizarrely named his dog as his successor.
A gritty squad of <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> shop owners who never quit.\nTheir stamina's off the charts, and they're tougher than you'd expect.
Based around a seaside inlet, this group of grade-schoolers plays\nlike pros. Many could easily go toe-to-toe with middle schoolers.
Kids from a dying tourist village at the foot of Saga's mountains.\nWhile friendly to visitors, their smiles have a creepy edge.
A top international squad known as Kyushu's strongest, packed\nwith players bigger and tougher than most high school teams.
Year after year, they dominate the Football Frontier undefeated,\nfull of elite talent and backed by pro-level training.
They tailor diverse strategies to every opponent.\nWith no fixed patterns, staying flexible is essential.
[南雲原/なぐもはら]サッカー[部/ぶ]の[特出点/とくしゅつてん]テキスト２。
They tailor diverse strategies to every opponent.\nWith no fixed patterns, staying flexible is essential.
They stick to one formation to handle shifting tactics,\nbut the <FLC:SHINANO> Formation weakens defence and synergy.
A fundamentally sound team with no clear weaknesses.\nOne playmaker runs the show, and the keeper has a signature move.
Two Keshin create an unstoppable offence-defence line.\nThe only way to fight back is with Keshin of your own.
They use a wide variety of tactics on offence and defence.\nBeating their perfect strategy takes creativity and unpredictability.
Their slick formation moves like a swarm of worker bees.\nPrecise passing and tight ball control keep them in charge.
Despite their rough look, they're tight-knit and work well together.\nConstant drills sharpen their basic skills.
Their rough style leads to plenty of dirty plays,\nbut when The Second calls the shots, the whole game can flip.
They play hard and fast, smashing through defences\nbut leaving gaps when they're back on defence.
These kids play way above their grade-school level.\nSmall builds mean their stamina fades as the game goes on.
Raised in the countryside, these players have solid endurance.\nThey dig deep in the second half, so get ahead early.
With top physical and instinctive skills, they rarely use tactics.\nTheir predictable style can be countered with smart strategy.
Each player is a force to be reckoned with, but clear-cut roles\nmake them easy to read. Countering their strengths is key.
The baseball players who did the after-school show all come from\nfootball backgrounds, with solid fitness built by tough training.
Their harsh daily training has boosted their physical strength,\nand their speed on the pitch is no joke.
A nigh-unstoppable team of stars led by a lone-wolf captain,\nwhose plans crumble if their carefully calculated plays are disrupted.
Each player exudes pressure and presence,\ncapable of swinging the entire match with a single decisive move.
They play clean to win the referee's favor while completely\nshutting down opponents' rough tactics to dominate the field.
Masters of combining multiple Special Moves, their balanced\nteamwork commands respect from every corner of the pitch.
A club in <FUL:ENDO>'s era that nearly\nsplit but instead became legends.
An elite team undefeated for 40 years,\ndisciplined under <FLC:YUTO>'s command.
The strongest team, led by Aphrody, is\nsaid to reach beyond-human levels.
Second rank of Alius Academy. The first\nextraterrestrials to descend to Earth.
First rank of Alius Academy. <FUL:DEZARM> leads\na team of skilled, unusual players.
Master rank of Alius Academy. The\nstrongest warriors with world-ruling power.
Japan's national team for the FFI\nWorld Cup, captained by <FUL:ENDO>.
The Raimon Eleven of <FST:TENMA>'s era\nwho fight to restore true football.
A supreme team formed by uniting\nEternal Light and Ancient Darkness.
Agents from the future's El Dorado,\nsent to erase football from history.
The ultimate eleven, united across\nspace and time to defend football.
A team of future outlaws assembled\nby the S-class threat <FST:ZANARK>.
Earth's team in the interplanetary\nGrand Celesta Galaxy tournament.
A fast-rising squad led by <FFC:UNMEI>,\ndefined by sharp tactics and rapid wins.

テスト[用/よう]サッカーバトルチーム[説明/せつめい]テキスト
A local baseball powerhouse. Back-to-back prefectural champs\nand national runners-up, they're the pride of their school.
Muscle comes first, period. They live by "no pain, no gain,"\nchasing the ultimate flex: the pose that makes any body look divine.
A sumo club with a girl at the helm. They've ditched outdated rules\nand just do it for the love of the ring.
Crowned Japan's top dance crew, they're the pride of the school.\nTheir energy, drive, and unity make them a force on any stage.
After merging with the stargazing club, their numbers grew,\nand so did the weirdness. They smile, chant, and try to talk to space.
No one gives handball the credit it deserves, so they've made\nit their mission to prove its worth. Every day's a grind for glory.
One of the school's oldest clubs, they quietly code games and apps.\nThe leader keeps taking random jobs, stressing everyone out.
A low-pressure club for kids who just want to play something.\nIt's packed, mostly thanks to the <FUL:GOMASHIO> duo.
What started as quiz prep turned into trivia overload.\nThey know manhole stats. And cat bloodlines. Seriously.
They all wear swim trunks under their uniforms—just in case waves hit.\nConstant shirtless sunning gets them labeled creeps by the girls.
A powerhouse in karuta, always near the top.\nTheir captain's nearly pro, and half of the Resplendent Duo.
Their captain was once a go prodigy... until he switched to shogi\nand tanked the whole vibe. Now the go crowd's quietly steaming.
Strong-ish. Popular-ish. They're the kinda club that fades\ninto the background, and even give up recruits to be polite.
Huge hit at school fests, but totally split:\none half wants to get serious, the other's just here for fun.
They don't recruit—"A samurai chooses their path."\nBut plenty still join, drawn to that lone-wolf honor.
They'll bust out new tricks anywhere,\nwhich kinda comes off as harassment to the rest of the school.
A classy, old-school club with perfect manners. The captain\nnever dances... but they say she knows one no one else does.
Obsessed with finding true beauty, they'll do anything for art;\neven dunk a car in a pond.
Smart. Stoic. Surprisingly unpopular. Once you meet them,\nyou'll get why they're known as the Handsome Yet Hopeless Bunch.
They keep a Peach Paradise Cup said to bring luck,\nand boost your grades. Not that anyone's brave enough to try.
Gunning for the top at the youth martial arts tourney, Divine Cup.\nWannabe tough guys drop by, only to get flattened.
The "Witch of Kyushu" leads the strongest team around. Rumor says\nshe can teleport and speak with her mind. She might be legit.
They've got a hit 4-panel comic in the school paper, but every year,\na fierce fight breaks out over who gets to run the next one.
Just chill ping-pong games with their advisor. No big dreams,\nno pressure... yet somehow, they still rack up wins.
Less occult lovers, more mad science buffs. They devote themselves\nto solving paranormal mysteries with cold, hard logic.
Fired-up but fractured, they argue across events. Some are even\npushing to scrap it all and just become the Pole Vault Club.
No stars, no wins, no presence. Most joined to get popular,\nbut now it's just a pack of unpopular kids wondering what went wrong.
A hybrid culture club for fans of metals: trains, ores, robots.\nThey try to convert metalhead music fans using catchy, upbeat songs.
Stoic swimmers who live and breathe pure speed, locked in an intense,\nyears-long turf war with the water polo club for pool supremacy.
Idol hopefuls and producer wannabes team up here. Romance often\nsparks, only to be busted wide open by the school paper every time.
Their tennis is like a stage drama: elegant and full of flair.\nMost are social butterflies, many already debuted in high society.
Firm believers that muscle counts in gaming too, they train with\npassion, confusing others who often mistake them for an athletic club.
This fierce group craves combat in the pool, not just laps; their\nbattle cries echo loudly, earning them harsh glares from the swimmers.
They recruit hard to fill the band. Their best pitch? "You'll get to\ncheer for the super popular baseball team!"—and it works.
Famed for the cursed chorus "It Will Come." Anyone who crosses\na member almost always faces sudden misfortune the very next day.
Once a lively club, they now struggle as passionate new talent\nkeeps getting recruited by other teams before they can even join.
Long ignored, they teamed up with the computer club to run\nthe school's SNS paper, now controlling all campus info.
Based in the aquaculture building, they study sea life. Their dream?\nTo capture and research the legendary <FUL:UMIBOZU>.
This team breaks the game down with cutting-edge tech. They learn\nso fast, folks are starting to wonder if their manager is an AI.
They stick to old-school traditions and a timeless style.\nEveryone's studied them to death, but they still find ways to win.
No fouls. No cheap shots. Just pure, clean football.\nThese self-disciplined saints play fair—and still rack up wins.
They may look humble, but don't be fooled. This Football Frontier\nregular has delivered some of the fiercest matches.
